int32 rtk_GetFxsEvent ( uint32  chid,
SIGNSTATE *  pval 
)

Get the FXS state.

This API translates value from rtk_GetSlicEvent(), and
does some additional DSP settings.
Thus, it can be seen as: rtk_GetFxsEvent() = rtk_GetSlicEvent() + rtk_GetDtmfEvent() + additional DSP settings

Parameters
chidThe channel number.
pvalThe phone state. Please refer to SIGNSTATE for more detail states.
Return values
0Success
See Also
rtk_OffHookAction, rtk_OnHookAction
Examples:
conference.c, custom_tone.c, fxo.c, fxs.c, phone.c, and rtp.c.
int32 rtk_GetFxoEvent ( uint32  chid,
SIGNSTATE *  pval 
)

Get the FXO state.

This API translates value from rtk_GetDaaEvent(), and
does some additional DSP settings.
Thus, it can be seen as: rtk_GetFxoEvent() = rtk_GetDaaEvent() + additional DSP settings

Parameters
chidThe channel number.
pvalThe FXO state. Please refer to SIGNSTATE for more detail states.
Return values
0Success
See Also
rtk_OffHookAction, rtk_OnHookAction
Examples:
fxo.c.

int32 rtk_SetDaaIsrFlow ( unsigned int  chid,
unsigned int  sid,
unsigned int  flow 
)

Set the DAA ISR Flow.

Parameters
chidThe channel number
sidThe session number. Usually 0 for master session, 1 for slave(conference) session.
flowThe DAA ISR Flow
0: Normal
1: PSTN 3-way conference
2: PSTN call forward
Return values
1Success
0xFFLine not connect or busy or not support
Note
Virtual DAA not support
